<h1>Scripts</h1>

<p style="color:#999; font-size:1.05rem; margin-bottom:3rem;">Animated explainer scripts — written and storyboarded, not yet produced. Each one is a self-contained piece: narration, visual direction, the actual code that appears on screen. The production pipeline (Remotion, ElevenLabs, FFmpeg) is spec'd out but the recordings haven't happened yet.</p>

<div style="margin-bottom:3rem; padding:1.5rem; border:1px solid #222; background:#0a0a0a;">
  <div style="color:#666; font-size:0.85rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.1em; margin-bottom:1rem;">Three Series</div>
  <div style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <span style="color:#e8e4de; font-weight:600;">How It Works</span> <span style="color:#555;">&middot; 5-8 min</span><br>
    <span style="color:#888; font-size:0.95rem;">One system per video. Architecture diagrams + real code walkthrough.</span>
  </div>
  <div style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <span style="color:#e8e4de; font-weight:600;">What I Learned From...</span> <span style="color:#555;">&middot; 3-5 min</span><br>
    <span style="color:#888; font-size:0.95rem;">Personal stories with principles. Incident first, framework second.</span>
  </div>
  <div>
    <span style="color:#e8e4de; font-weight:600;">The Code</span> <span style="color:#555;">&middot; 2-3 min</span><br>
    <span style="color:#888; font-size:0.95rem;">One concept. One code snippet. One principle.</span>
  </div>
</div>

